Two hearts beat as one.

00:00:25.892 --> 00:00:27.393
Matches up perfectly.

00:00:27.493 --> 00:00:30.062
-(DISTORTED SOUND)
-That's a match.

00:00:30.162 --> 00:00:31.698
-(COMPUTER BEEPS)
-MAN 1: We've got a match.

00:00:31.798 --> 00:00:32.865
MAN 2: And it just found
us a match.

00:00:32.965 --> 00:00:34.033
WOMAN 1: Visible match.

00:00:34.133 --> 00:00:35.401
-WOMAN 2: We've a match.
-Match.

00:00:35.501 --> 00:00:36.636
MAN 3: Were you able
to determine

00:00:36.736 --> 00:00:37.837
which monkey bit him?

00:00:37.937 --> 00:00:38.938
The bite marks match

00:00:39.038 --> 00:00:40.573
those of the monkey found
at the scene.

00:00:40.840 --> 00:00:41.941
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)
-Wow!

00:00:42.608 --> 00:00:43.943
That last one was presumably

00:00:44.043 --> 00:00:45.979
from one of the crossover
episodes where the team

00:00:46.079 --> 00:00:47.080
from<i> Law &amp; Order,</i>

00:00:47.447 --> 00:00:50.283
worked a case with the cast
of Monkey Law and Monkey Order.

00:00:50.383 --> 00:00:52.318
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)
-(MONKEY SCREECHES)

00:00:52.418 --> 00:00:53.820
-But...
-(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

00:00:54.187 --> 00:00:57.356
on TV and in real life
forensic science plays

00:00:57.456 --> 00:00:59.392
an important role
in criminal convictions.

00:00:59.492 --> 00:01:02.995
Prosecutors often complain
about a so called C.S.I. effect,

00:01:03.195 --> 00:01:06.365
where jurors expect to see
forensic evidence in every case.

00:01:06.465 --> 00:01:08.835
The problem is,
not all forensic science

00:01:08.935 --> 00:01:11.438
is as reliable as we've become
accustomed to believe.

00:01:11.538 --> 00:01:12.939
A report in 2009,

00:01:13.039 --> 00:01:14.874
by the National Academy
of Sciences found that

00:01:14.974 --> 00:01:16.176
many forensic scientists

00:01:16.276 --> 00:01:19.012
do not meet the fundamental
requirements of science.

00:01:19.112 --> 00:01:20.179
And a report last year

00:01:20.279 --> 00:01:22.415
by a Presidential Science
Council agreed saying that,

00:01:22.615 --> 00:01:24.617
"expert witnesses have often
overstated

00:01:24.717 --> 00:01:27.319
the value of their evidence,
going far beyond

00:01:27.419 --> 00:01:29.388
what the relevant science
can justify,"

00:01:29.488 --> 00:01:30.756
and that's the thing here.

00:01:30.856 --> 00:01:33.092
It's not that
all forensic science is bad,

00:01:33.292 --> 00:01:35.227
'cause it's not, but too often,

00:01:35.327 --> 00:01:37.997
it's reliability
is dangerously overstated

00:01:38.097 --> 00:01:40.600
and one sign of that is that
forensic experts in court

00:01:40.700 --> 00:01:43.802
are often nudged to use one
very convincing phrase.

00:01:44.303 --> 00:01:46.705
MAN 4: To a reasonable degree
of the scientific certainty...

00:01:46.805 --> 00:01:48.607
To a reasonable degree
of scientific certainty...

00:01:48.707 --> 00:01:50.677
MAN 5: To a reasonable degree
of the scientific certainty...

00:01:50.777 --> 00:01:53.512 line:0%
Within reasonable
scientific certainty...

00:01:53.612 --> 00:01:55.948 line:0%
To a reasonable degree
of scientific certainty...

00:01:56.148 --> 00:01:58.684
MAN 6: Are you able to say that
within a reasonable degree

00:01:58.784 --> 00:02:00.853
-of the scientific certainty?
-Yes.

00:02:01.387 --> 00:02:02.722
And here's the thing that phrase

00:02:02.822 --> 00:02:05.158
does have a persuasive ring
to it. Unfortunately,

00:02:05.258 --> 00:02:07.093
as that Presidential Council
pointed out,

00:02:07.193 --> 00:02:10.396
it has no generally accepted
meaning in science.

00:02:10.596 --> 00:02:13.232
It's one of those terms
like, basic or trill

00:02:13.433 --> 00:02:16.001
that has no commonly
understood definition.

00:02:16.202 --> 00:02:17.469
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)
-Am I trill?

00:02:17.569 --> 00:02:18.704
Is that good or bad?

00:02:18.804 --> 00:02:21.840
I mean I do feel trill,
so I'm guessing it's awful.

00:02:21.941 --> 00:02:25.110
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)
-And-- when bad science

00:02:25.210 --> 00:02:28.080
is confidently presented,
terrible convictions can happen.

00:02:28.180 --> 00:02:29.982
In fact, among the hundreds
of people

00:02:30.082 --> 00:02:32.785
who have been exonerated
by DNA testing since 1989,

00:02:32.885 --> 00:02:34.921
in nearly half of their cases,

00:02:35.021 --> 00:02:37.289
there was some misapplication
of forensic science

00:02:37.490 --> 00:02:39.492
and there are people
behind those numbers.

00:02:39.726 --> 00:02:42.295
Take Santae Tribble, who was
convicted of murder

00:02:42.395 --> 00:02:44.630
and served 26 years.
In large part,

00:02:44.864 --> 00:02:47.300
thanks to an FBI analyst
who testified that his hair

00:02:47.500 --> 00:02:48.735
matched hairs found
at the scene.

00:02:48.835 --> 00:02:49.869
And as he will tell you,

00:02:49.969 --> 00:02:52.538
the evidence was presented,
as being rock solid.

00:02:53.039 --> 00:02:55.208 line:0%
They said they matched my hair

00:02:55.408 --> 00:02:57.843 line:0%
in all microscopical
characteristics.

00:02:58.577 --> 00:03:01.213
<i> And that's the way
 they presented it to the jury</i>

00:03:01.313 --> 00:03:05.051
and the jury took it for granted
that, that was my hair.

00:03:05.584 --> 00:03:07.520
But you know, I can see,
why they did.

00:03:07.620 --> 00:03:10.189
Because who other
than an FBI expert

00:03:10.456 --> 00:03:12.525
would possibly know
that much about hair?

00:03:12.625 --> 00:03:13.626
Except of course,

00:03:13.826 --> 00:03:17.096
whoever stalled Amanda Seyfried
at the 2009 Oscars.

00:03:17.363 --> 00:03:18.564
Breath taking waves,

00:03:18.665 --> 00:03:21.000
without loosing
any of their body or bounce.

00:03:21.300 --> 00:03:23.035
-Stunning.
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

00:03:23.269 --> 00:03:25.604
-Stunning!
-(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

00:03:25.704 --> 00:03:27.339
-Stunning.
-(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

00:03:27.540 --> 00:03:28.774
-Stunning.
-(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

00:03:28.874 --> 00:03:31.143
Stunning! Stunning! Stunning!
Stunning! Stunning! Stunning!

00:03:31.243 --> 00:03:32.378
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

00:03:32.612 --> 00:03:35.782
The jurors in Tribble's case,
were actually told

00:03:35.882 --> 00:03:37.784
there was one chance
in ten million

00:03:37.884 --> 00:03:39.986
that it could be someone
else's hair, and guess what?

00:03:40.086 --> 00:03:41.354
He was exonerated.

00:03:41.587 --> 00:03:44.590
Because once DNA analysis became
available, his lawyer tested

00:03:44.690 --> 00:03:46.158
the thirteen hairs from the case

00:03:46.258 --> 00:03:48.461
and not only were
none of them his,

00:03:48.761 --> 00:03:50.762
some of what they found
was incredible.

00:03:50.963 --> 00:03:52.899
SANDRA LEVICK:<i> Nine of the
 hairs had come from the
 same source,</i>

00:03:53.099 --> 00:03:55.067 line:0%
a couple had come
from different sources

00:03:55.167 --> 00:03:56.202 line:0%
and one was a dog.

00:03:56.402 --> 00:03:58.504 line:0%
INTERVIEWER: Two different
FBI agents who had, eh,

00:03:58.604 --> 00:04:01.107 line:0%
looked at that and analyzed it,
didn't recognize that it was

00:04:01.207 --> 00:04:02.709
-dog hair?
-It was a K9.

00:04:03.876 --> 00:04:05.611
It was a domestic dog, yes.

00:04:05.711 --> 00:04:08.381
My personal conclusion was,

00:04:08.581 --> 00:04:11.818
-the dog committed the crime.
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

00:04:12.585 --> 00:04:13.519
Okay.

00:04:13.919 --> 00:04:17.055
So, first, it is amazing that
he is able to laugh at that,

00:04:17.322 --> 00:04:19.425
but second, if a dog did
commit the crime

00:04:19.525 --> 00:04:22.528
there's really no recourse there
because there is actually no law

00:04:22.628 --> 00:04:24.163
against dogs committing murder

00:04:24.264 --> 00:04:26.365
and that's a fact
that learned in<i> Air Bud 9,</i>

00:04:26.465 --> 00:04:27.566
<i> Fuck the Paw-lice!</i>

00:04:27.666 --> 00:04:29.102
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)
-And--

00:04:29.469 --> 00:04:30.503
it turns out,

00:04:30.803 --> 00:04:33.739
Tribble is not the only case
where FBI experts

00:04:33.840 --> 00:04:35.875
overstated their confidence
in their results.

00:04:36.375 --> 00:04:37.609 line:0%
NEWSCASTER:
<i> The Innocence Project</i>

00:04:37.709 --> 00:04:40.413
<i> and the National Association
 of Criminal Defense lawyers</i>

00:04:40.513 --> 00:04:43.583
<i> found from the 1970's
 through 1999,</i>

00:04:43.683 --> 00:04:48.387
