-(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)
-And look,

00:05:23.455 --> 00:05:24.556
it's by no means,

00:05:24.657 --> 00:05:26.825
just microscopic hair
comparison which has had

00:05:26.926 --> 00:05:28.727
the reliability
of these results overstated.

00:05:28.827 --> 00:05:30.462
Those reports that
I showed earlier suggests

00:05:30.562 --> 00:05:31.897
there is weak scientific support

00:05:31.997 --> 00:05:33.466
for some aspects
of techniques like

00:05:33.566 --> 00:05:37.636
a blood pattern, footwear,
firearm and bite mark analysis.

00:05:37.836 --> 00:05:39.972
And you must be familiar
with that last one from

00:05:40.072 --> 00:05:41.673
cool scenes like this:

00:05:42.274 --> 00:05:45.944
A little 3D magic for clarity
and I give you

00:05:46.211 --> 00:05:47.713
the killer's incisors.

00:05:47.913 --> 00:05:53.453
(COMPUTER BEEPING)

00:05:53.852 --> 00:05:54.887
Oh, Yo!

00:05:55.120 --> 00:05:57.757
The computer rated
it "Yellow rectangle."

00:05:57.957 --> 00:06:00.960
And we all know yellow rectangle
is the highest level of match

00:06:01.060 --> 00:06:02.861
a computer can
give you about teeth.

00:06:02.961 --> 00:06:03.963
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

00:06:04.063 --> 00:06:06.132
Look, in the real world,
bite mark analysis

00:06:06.232 --> 00:06:08.033
is highly subjective
and unreliable.

00:06:08.133 --> 00:06:10.436
The President's Council found
the entire discipline,

00:06:10.536 --> 00:06:12.504
does not meet
the scientific standards

00:06:12.604 --> 00:06:14.407
for foundational validity.

00:06:14.507 --> 00:06:17.743
Which I believe, is science
speak for "Bullshit!"

00:06:18.444 --> 00:06:20.146
But people have been sent
to prison

00:06:20.246 --> 00:06:22.648
on the basis of bite mark
testimony by experts like,

00:06:22.748 --> 00:06:23.949
Dr. Michael West.

00:06:24.416 --> 00:06:27.753 line:0%
The science of bite marks
analysis, is very accurate.

00:06:27.853 --> 00:06:29.188 line:0%
NARRATOR 1:<i> When it comes
 to bite marks,</i>

00:06:29.288 --> 00:06:31.390 line:0%
<i> West consider himself
 "The maestro."</i>

00:06:31.624 --> 00:06:34.193 line:0%
<i> He's found bite marks
 on a decomposed body</i>

00:06:34.293 --> 00:06:35.528 line:0%
<i> submerged in a swamp,</i>

00:06:35.828 --> 00:06:38.664 line:0%
<i>on a corpse that had been buried
 for more than a year.</i>

00:06:38.864 --> 00:06:40.265 line:0%
<i> He's even used a bite mark</i>

00:06:40.365 --> 00:06:42.935 line:0%
<i>taken out of a bologna sandwich
 to get a conviction.</i>

00:06:43.168 --> 00:06:46.071
Now, that sounds impressive
matching a killer's teeth

00:06:46.171 --> 00:06:47.706
to a bite mark
in a bologna sandwich,

00:06:47.806 --> 00:06:49.976
although, you should know
that the defendant in that case,

00:06:50.076 --> 00:06:52.044
got a new trial
after an autopsy report

00:06:52.144 --> 00:06:53.345
found that the murder victim

00:06:53.445 --> 00:06:55.748
had actually eaten
a small amount of bologna

00:06:55.848 --> 00:06:58.217
consistent with the amounts
bitten off the sandwich.

00:06:58.317 --> 00:06:59.485
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)
-So, that sandwich,

00:06:59.685 --> 00:07:01.453
was irrelevant to the case.

00:07:01.553 --> 00:07:04.723
In fact, you could even argue
that it was actually Dr. West,

00:07:04.823 --> 00:07:06.792
who was full of, say it with me,

00:07:07.126 --> 00:07:08.660
-shit.
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

00:07:08.760 --> 00:07:11.163
And-- that
is not the only issue

00:07:11.263 --> 00:07:12.531
that has arisen
from his testimony.

00:07:12.631 --> 00:07:14.167
There are now five cases

00:07:14.367 --> 00:07:15.835
where he testified
for the prosecution

00:07:15.935 --> 00:07:17.302
and where the charges
were dropped

00:07:17.402 --> 00:07:18.971
or the conviction was
later over turned

00:07:19.071 --> 00:07:20.373
and even West himself

00:07:20.573 --> 00:07:22.508
has admitted that
he no longer believes

00:07:22.708 --> 00:07:25.745
in bite mark analysis
for identifying perpetrators

00:07:25.845 --> 00:07:27.679
and he doesn't think it should
be used in court.

00:07:27.779 --> 00:07:29.115
And yet, incredibly,

00:07:29.215 --> 00:07:31.784
every time a defendant
has challenged its validity

00:07:31.884 --> 00:07:33.819
the court has
ruled it admissible.

00:07:34.019 --> 00:07:35.955
And a key reason for that

00:07:36.055 --> 00:07:38.190
is that judges often rely
on precedent

00:07:38.290 --> 00:07:40.325
to decide what to allow
in front of a jury. So,

00:07:40.425 --> 00:07:43.061
if a particular discipline
has been in court before

00:07:43.162 --> 00:07:45.398
it is likely that a judge
will admit it again.

00:07:45.498 --> 00:07:47.633
All of which means
that as the co-founder

00:07:47.733 --> 00:07:49.301
of the Innocence Project
points out,

00:07:49.568 --> 00:07:52.171
decisions about the validity
of science are being made

00:07:52.271 --> 00:07:55.174
by people who don't necessarily
know much about it.

00:07:55.608 --> 00:07:58.310 line:0%
Historically, we had
a situation where,

00:07:58.577 --> 00:08:00.879 line:0%
two scientifically
illiterate lawyers

00:08:01.247 --> 00:08:04.216
argued the bonafides
of scientific evidence

00:08:04.416 --> 00:08:06.485
before a scientifically
illiterate judge,

00:08:06.719 --> 00:08:09.355
so the 12 scientifically
illiterate jurors

00:08:09.655 --> 00:08:11.423
could decide the weight
of that evidence.

00:08:11.990 --> 00:08:14.760
And if you think about it,
that's absolutely terrifying.

00:08:14.861 --> 00:08:17.429
Trials can often be a situation
when no one

00:08:17.529 --> 00:08:18.998
really knows
what they are doing.

00:08:19.098 --> 00:08:21.199
It's like a cooking competition
for toddlers,

00:08:21.400 --> 00:08:24.403
hosted by a stray cat
and judged by goats.

00:08:24.503 --> 00:08:25.504
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)
-Oh.

00:08:25.604 --> 00:08:26.906
The tuna was under cooked

00:08:27.006 --> 00:08:28.741
and covered
in cold spaghetti sauce.

00:08:28.841 --> 00:08:29.808
You then for some reason

00:08:29.908 --> 00:08:32.110
cover the whole dish
in honey nut cheerios.

00:08:32.511 --> 00:08:34.646
-I loved it.
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

00:08:34.880 --> 00:08:36.682
And look, none of this
is to say,

00:08:36.782 --> 00:08:39.251
that there is not reliable
forensic science out there.

00:08:39.351 --> 00:08:41.019
Finger prints and DNA

00:08:41.219 --> 00:08:43.822
are obvious examples but while
we think of them as perfect,

00:08:43.922 --> 00:08:45.190
it is important to know

00:08:45.290 --> 00:08:47.459
they are by no means infallible.

00:08:47.559 --> 00:08:49.528
The FBI has found
fingerprint analysis

00:08:49.628 --> 00:08:50.830
could have a false positive rate

00:08:50.930 --> 00:08:53.699
as high as one error
in 306 cases.

00:08:53.799 --> 00:08:55.334
And a dramatic example of this

00:08:55.434 --> 00:08:58.137
came after the Madrid's
train bombings in 2004

00:08:58.237 --> 00:09:02.074
when the FBI arrested this
Oregon man, Brandon Mayfield.

00:09:02.174 --> 00:09:05.177
He had never even
been to Spain in his life.

00:09:05.478 --> 00:09:09.081
But, three separate examiners,
matched his finger prints

00:09:09.181 --> 00:09:11.917
to one on a bag of detonators.
So, he was at that point,

00:09:12.184 --> 00:09:13.785
completely fucked!

00:09:14.052 --> 00:09:16.522
Until, investigators happen
to determine that,

00:09:16.622 --> 00:09:19.658
that fingerprint actually
also matched someone else

00:09:19.958 --> 00:09:22.661
who was in Spain at the time
and that blew the minds

00:09:22.861 --> 00:09:24.263
of finger print experts.

00:09:24.797 --> 00:09:25.798
MARK ACREE:
<i> We always assume</i>

00:09:25.898 --> 00:09:28.066
<i> that finger prints
 are very very unique,</i>

00:09:28.600 --> 00:09:32.237
<i> but what the Mayfield case
 demonstrates, is that</i>

00:09:32.604 --> 00:09:35.040 line:0%
parts of a fingerprint
can be

00:09:35.141 --> 00:09:38.510 line:0%
so similar, it's possible
for two people to be

00:09:38.710 --> 00:09:41.346
<i> identified to one print.</i>

00:09:41.613 --> 00:09:42.682
That's true.

00:09:42.782 --> 00:09:44.817
It turns out that two people
can have finger prints

00:09:44.917 --> 00:09:47.320
that are so close that even
experts can't tell them apart.

00:09:47.420 --> 00:09:49.288
Meaning that we are
now this close

00:09:49.555 --> 00:09:53.525
to finally proving my theory.
There is only one Olsen twin.

00:09:53.892 --> 00:09:55.861
She's just moving very fast

00:09:55.961 --> 00:09:56.962
-back and forth.
-(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

00:09:57.062 --> 00:09:58.297
She confuses your eye.

00:09:58.397 --> 00:10:00.933
Now, I don't know how this
new information helps me, yet,

00:10:01.033 --> 00:10:04.636
but when it does, the end is--
No! You frauds! You frauds!

00:10:04.903 --> 00:10:07.973
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

00:10:08.240 --> 00:10:10.609
And then-- there is DNA,

00:10:10.709 --> 00:10:13.512
